content.text: Barack Obama is a former U.S. president who served from 2009 to 2017. He was the first African-American president and a member of the Democratic Party. Prior to becoming president, he served as a U.S. senator from Illinois from 2005 to 2008 and as an Illinois state senator from 1997 to 2004.
